%U A394939 3031684807,9150419507,27681787565,83920834001,254919014123,775769113935,2364871114713,7220699241477,22080269030319,67615034329515
%N A394939 Number of well-formed bracketed words of total length n built from the symbol * (of length 1) and two unary bracket types, with no empty bracket pair.
%C A394939 A well-formed bracketed word is a properly nested word using the symbol * together with two types of matching unary brackets; the condition "no empty bracket pair" means that every matching bracket pair encloses at least one symbol.
%C A394939 Under this interpretation there is no object of total length 0, hence the sequence is naturally indexed from n=1.
%C A394939 Equivalently, a(n) is the number of operator monomials of total length n generated from one indeterminate * by associative multiplication and two noncommuting unary operators P_1, P_2, where * has length 1 and each application of P_i contributes 2 to the total length.
%C A394939 Equivalently, for n>=1, a(n) counts peakless Motzkin paths of length n with 2-colored up steps; here "peakless" means that the path contains no occurrence of UD.
%H A394939 Yu Hin Au and Murray R. Bremner, <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2604.25731">Enumerating Multi-Operator Monomials in Commutative and Noncommutative Settings</a>, arXiv:2604.25731 [math.CO], 2026.
%F A394939 G.f.: 1 + A(x) satisfies A(x) = x + x*A(x) + 2*x^2*A(x) + 2*x^2*A(x)^2.
%F A394939 G.f.: 1 + A(x) = (1 - x - 2*x^2 - sqrt((1 - x - 2*x^2)^2 - 8*x^3))/(4*x^2).
%F A394939 a(n) = Sum_{k=0..floor((n-1)/2)} 2^k*N(n-k,k), where N(m,k) = A001263(m,k) = binomial(m,k)*binomial(m,k+1)/m are the Narayana numbers.
%F A394939 a(0)=a(1)=1; for n>=2, a(n) = a(n-1) + 2*a(n-2) + 2*Sum_{i=1..n-3} a(i)*a(n-2-i), with a(m)=0 for m<=0.
%e A394939 For n=4, a(4)=7. In bracketed-word form (using () for P_1 and [] for P_2), the 7 objects are ****, (*)*, *(*), (**), [*]*, *[*], [**].
%Y A394939 Cf. A001263, A004148, A394940, A394941, A001003.
